Restoration algorithms also consider the unconstrained problem:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\min_{u\in\mathbb{R}^{n}}\frac{1}{2}\|Au-f\|_{2}^{2}+\tau\phi(u)\label{eq:alternative_problem}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

The formulation (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:constrained-1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

) has the benefit that the parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

 has a clear meaning, i.e.
 it is proportional to the noise standard deviation 
