key "Yun-2017,Afonso-2011"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, the focus is on ADMM (or 
\emph on
alternate direction method of multipliers) 
\emph default
to solve the minimization problem.
 ADMM is described in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Boyd-2010"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

an algorithm that is intended to blend the decomposability of dual ascent
 with the superior convergence properties of the method of multipliers
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, and has a close relationship with Douglas-Rachford iterative schemes.
 In section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Theoretical-Properties"
plural "false"
