 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 be the number of iterations.
 We observe the following for Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:KADMM-TV"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Constructing the Arnoldi basis via Gram-Schmidt orthogonalization takes
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}(m^{2}n)$
\end_inset

 operations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In each iteration, a least squares problem of size 
\begin_inset Formula $(3m+1)\times m$
\end_inset

 is solved, with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}((3m+1)^{2}m)$
\end_inset

 operations (using QR decomposition).
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
This is much smaller than the least squares problem from a direct application
 of ADMM, with size 
\begin_inset Formula $3n\times n$
\end_inset

 and complexity 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}(9n^{3})$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The product 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{m}\alpha$
\end_inset

 takes 
\begin_inset Formula $mn$
\end_inset

 operations.
 In each iteration, the result can be stored and reused.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The product 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{m+1}H_{m}\alpha$
\end_inset

 requires 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}(2m^{2}+2mn)$
\end_inset

 operations, compared to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}(2mn+2n^{2})$
\end_inset

 for the product 
\begin_inset Formula $AQ_{m}\alpha$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The projection onto 
\begin_inset Formula $B(\epsilon,f)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $[0,1]^{n}$
\end_inset

 takes 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}(n)$
\end_inset

 operations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Condat's taut string algorithm has worst-case complexity 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}(n^{2})$
\end_inset

, with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}(n)$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

in all practical situations
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

