\begin_layout Standard
For the three types of blur described in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Spatially-variant-Gaussian"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, we applied KADDM to images with varying degrees of noise.
 To measure the quality of the restoration, we used the mean squared error
 between restored image 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{u}$
\end_inset

 and original image 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\text{MSE}=\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}(u_{i}-\hat{u}_{i}).
\]

\end_inset

Parameters for Algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "alg:KADMM-TV"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 were chosen as follows.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The initial values for 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{i}$
\end_inset

 are sampled from the uniform distribution 
\begin_inset Formula $U[0,1]$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The order 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 of the Krylov subspace is set to 16, to limit memory requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Relative change of residuals was used for the termination criterium, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\|r^{i}-r^{i-1}\|/\|r\|<\text{TOL},$
\end_inset

 with a tolerance of 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{-6}$
\end_inset

 and a maximum amount of iterations of 10,000.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The authors in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Yun-2017"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 suggest 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon=\sqrt{\tau MN}\sigma$
\end_inset

 using Morozov's discrepancy principle, with 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau=1$
\end_inset

.
 Following 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Chuan-2014"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, we used a fixed 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau<1$
\end_inset

 to avoid an oversmoothed image.
\end_layout

